## Introduction

How much do YY male EBT measure and grow after their introduction in the wild? Is there a relationship between growth/size and the distance fish have moved? We examined size and changes in growth of YY EBT males during the time between their first release in the wild and at recapture after one year between the years 2018-2022. We examined the associations with possible interfering factors such as size at release, condition, site of release, group of release, timing of release and extent of movement, in order to pinpoint the factors that may contribute to (or inhibit) YY male EBT growth during the first year in the wild. We examined how growth differential and growth rate could be affected by differences in grouping or timing of release, and whether size at first release would have a significant effect on the growth of introduced YY EBT males. We also included in the analysis the condition factor K, measured as:
$$
k = \frac{\text{weight} \times 10^5}{\text{length}^3}
$$
an index of the relative degree of plumpness of the fish (Tyus, 2012). We also asked whether fish that had negative AG and IGR significantly differed in size at release or distance moved from those with positive growths.

